useradd — create a new user

SYNOPSIS
  useradd [--admin] NAME

DESCRIPTION
  Creates a new entry in /etc/passwd with a PBKDF2-hashed password and
  a default capability set that depends on the role:

    --admin   caps = {"*"} — full privileges. The user can sudo.
    (none)    limited set:
              syscall:exec
              syscall:write:/home/<name>/*
              syscall:write:/tmp/*
              component:* (gpu, screen, keyboard, internet, modem,
                           tunnel, data, filesystem:*)
              ipc:channel:*

  The home directory /home/<name> is created best-effort; failure to
  create it is not fatal (the boot fs may be read-only in dev).

  Capability enforcement defaults to true (/etc/security.cfg). Until
  the first user is created, sessiond drops to a privileged root shell
  with caps={"*"}; immediately after `useradd` the next login follows
  the limited-cap regime.

SEE ALSO
  passwd(1), userdel(1), sudo(1), security(5)
